history.content: This is kind of a dumb question but looking at the academic guide, there is no specification exactly what "upper division EECS courses" are for the 20 units that need to count towards an EECS major. I always presumed it was just any course that starts with EL ENG, COMPSCI, or EECS, including those that are cross-listed like CompSci C100  but I would like some clarification on this. Thanks!
history.subject: What counts as upper division EECS courses?
